title: Skippack Bridge
data: Skippack Bridge, also known as Montgomery County Bridge No. 142, is a historic stone arch bridge located near Evansburg in Lower Providence Township, Montgomery County, Pennsylvania. The bridge was built in 1792 and repaired in 1874. It has eight spans, is 33-foot  (10 m) wide, with an overall length of 202-foot  (62 m).  The bridge carries Germantown Pike across Skippack Creek.[2] It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1970.[1] This article about a property in Montgomery County, Pennsylvania on the National Register of Historic Places is a stub.
